    "body":  "Refine the Upload Qualifications page with small usability and visual polish enhancements to improve first impressions, reduce user friction, and subtly demonstrate design maturity during demos.\n\n✅ Enhancements to Implement\n**1. Add Drag-and-Drop Upload Option**\n\n**Behavior:** User should be able to either:\n\n- Click to open the file browser (existing behavior), or\n- Drag and drop a file directly into the upload area\n\n**Visual Prompt:**\n\n- Under the “Choose File” button, add: \n“Or drag your file here”\nStyle suggestion: light gray font, centered, subtle padding above/below\n\n**2. Intro Line Under “How It Works”**\n\n**Location:** Beneath the blue “How It Works” title\n\n**Text:**\n\n“Here’s how your document is securely processed and parsed using AI.”\n\n- Style: Smaller font (same as tips panel), medium gray\n\n**3. Subtle Entrance Animations**\n\n**Target Elements:**\n\n- 4 process icons in “How It Works” panel\n- Main upload icon (cloud)\n\n\n**Effect:**\n\n- Fade-in or slide-up animation on page load\n- Staggered delay (e.g., 150–200ms between steps)\n\n**Optional:** Use a CSS animation library like Animate.css for speed\n\n**Notes for Implementation:**\n\n- These enhancements are visual only (no backend logic changes required)\n- Static placeholder data is acceptable if needed for testing animations",
